com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Class SunriseControllerExecutionService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution.SunriseControllerExecutionService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMotionExecutionService, ICommandExecutionService, IOverridableRecovery, ISPRExecutorService, IExecutionService, IPausableExecutionService, com.kuka.threading.IDisposable

    public class SunriseControllerExecutionService
extends Object
implements IPausableExecutionService, ICommandExecutionService, IMotionExecutionService, ISPRExecutorService, IOverridableRecovery, com.kuka.threading.IDisposable
    Sunrise execution service. Maps commands to SPRs and sends them to Sunrise. It also handles the incoming message from Sunrise concerning SPR states and SPR data.

    This class is responsible for handling the main command protocol with Sunrise. Changes in the protocol must be reflected in this class.

    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

      • SunriseControllerExecutionService

        public SunriseControllerExecutionService(String controllerName,
                                         MapperConfiguration mapperConfiguration,
                                         IDeviceList deviceList,
                                         ISSRExecutor ssrExecutor,
                                         ISPRExecutor sprExecutor,
                                         IControllerSafety controllerSafety,
                                         ISunriseTools tools,
                                         ISunriseConnection connection,
                                         IApplicationStateStopRequestMappers stopRequestMappers,
                                         boolean pausable)
        Creates a new instance of the Sunrise execution service.
        Parameters:
        controllerName - name of the controller
        mapperConfiguration - parameter set with additional mapper configuration
        deviceList - device list of the controller for which the execution service is created
        ssrExecutor - the SSR executor to send SSR-s.
        sprExecutor - spr executor capability of controller
        controllerSafety - the controller safety to subscribe for safety state events.
        tools - sunrise tools providing utilities.
        connection - sunrise connection used for communication with sunrise real time core
        stopRequestMappers - for mapping additional stop request sources for the application state SPR.
        pausable - if set to true - execution service will respond to pause requests

      • executeSPRAsCommand

        @Deprecated
public ICommandContainer executeSPRAsCommand(SPR spr)
        Deprecated. the SunriseControllerExecutionService is intended to execute motions and will therefore only execute SPRs if it isn't paused. Thus, non-motion SPRs should be executed by obtaining the ISPRExecutor capability.
        Executes the specified SPR. Creates a container for the given SPR and returns it.

        The execution is asynchronous. However the method can block if the execution service is in paused state. Use the IExecutionContainer.await() method on the returned container to block until the SPR in done.

        Specified by:
        executeSPRAsCommand in interface ISPRExecutorService
        Parameters:
        spr - The SPR to be executed. null is not allowed.
        Returns:
        The container for the execution.
